section.section:
An employee appointed under this section may issue citations to the extent authorized by the Administration for violations of:
Those provisions of Title 13 of this article relating to:
Those provisions of Title 17 of this article relating to required security;
Those provisions of Title 14 of this article relating to falsified, altered, or forged documents and plates;
Those provisions of Title 16 of this article relating to unlawful application for a license and vehicle operation during periods of cancellation, revocation, and suspension of a driver's license;
Those provisions of Title 21 of this article relating to special residential parking permits issued by the Administration;
Those provisions of §§ 15-113 and 15-113.1 of this article relating to maintenance of and access to required business records;
Those provisions of Title 15 of this article relating to unlicensed business activity; and
Those provisions of this title relating to the issuance of an identification card.
